RABIES, HUMAN - TANZANIA
************************
A ProMED-mail post
Date: Sat, 20 Sep 1997 14:25:51 -0200
From: Luiz Jacintho da Silva <luisjs@guttenberg.correionet.com.br>
Source: Panafrican News Agency [http://www.africanews.org/PANA/science]
(September 17, 1997)

[It has been reported that there] were 20 human deaths by rabies in
southern Tanzania since early 1997. Apparently the disease was spread by
foxes. An effort to vaccinate approximately 4,500 dogs is under way and
should be accomplished by December.
